List, inspect, create, update, and change state for stored Codex credentials managed by rascald.

Usage:
  rascal auth credentials [flags]
  rascal auth credentials [command]

Examples:
rascal auth credentials list
rascal auth credentials create --auth-file ~/.codex/auth.json --scope personal
rascal auth credentials disable cred_123
rascal auth credentials cooldown cred_123 --for 30m --reason "upstream auth failures"

Available Commands:
  cooldown    Set or clear credential cooldown state
  create      Create a stored credential
  disable     Disable a stored credential
  enable      Enable a stored credential and clear manual cooldown state
  get         Show one stored credential
  list        List stored credentials visible to the current principal
  update      Update metadata or auth material for a stored credential

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for credentials

Global Flags:
      --api-token string              orchestrator API token
      --client-ssh-host string        SSH target host for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-key string         SSH private key path for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-port int           SSH target port for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-user string        SSH target user for API transport=ssh/auto
      --config string                 config file path (default "$HOME/.rascal/config.toml")
      --default-repo string           default repository in OWNER/REPO form
      --env-file string               env file path (fallback: ./.rascal.env if present)
      --github-runtime-token string   GitHub runtime token for remote auth sync
      --host string                   existing server host for remote auth sync
      --no-color                      disable ANSI color/style output (also set by NO_COLOR)
      --output string                 output format: table|json|toml (default "table")
  -q, --quiet                         reduce non-essential output
      --restart-service               restart active rascal slot after remote auth sync (default true)
      --server-url string             orchestrator URL
      --show                          print raw token values
      --ssh-key string                SSH private key path for remote auth sync
      --ssh-port int                  SSH target port for remote auth sync (default 22)
      --ssh-user string               SSH target user for remote auth sync (default "root")
      --transport string              API transport: auto|http|ssh
      --write-config                  write generated API token to local config

Use "rascal auth credentials [command] --help" for more information about a command.
